tags.name: Surreal Comedy
tags.description: Prominently features comedic moments that defy casual reasoning, resulting in illogical events.

tags.name: Twins
tags.description: Prominently features two or more siblings that were born at one birth.

tags.name: Family Life
tags.description: Centers around the activities of a family unit.

tags.name: Primarily Adult Cast
tags.description: Main cast is mostly composed of characters above a high school age.

tags.name: Artificial Intelligence
tags.description: Intelligent non-organic machines that work and react similarly to humans.

tags.name: Primarily Male Cast
tags.description: Main cast is mostly composed of male characters.

tags.name: Slapstick
tags.description: Prominently features comedy based on deliberately clumsy actions or embarrassing events.

tags.name: Satire
tags.description: Prominently features the use of comedy or ridicule to expose and criticise social phenomena.

tags.name: Episodic
tags.description: Features story arcs that are loosely tied or lack an overarching plot.

tags.name: Otaku Culture
tags.description: Centers around the culture of a fanatical fan-base.

tags.name: Meta
tags.description: Features fourth wall-breaking references to itself or genre tropes.

tags.name: Cute Boys Doing Cute Things
tags.description: Centers around male characters doing cute activities, usually with little to no emphasis on drama and conflict.

tags.name: Shounen
tags.description: Target demographic is teenage and young adult males.

node.description: [Website](https://aopanimelove.jp/) | [Blog](https://ameblo.jp/aop-blog/) | [Twitter](https://twitter.com/AOP_animelove) | [Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/aop201209) | [YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCnFnH7wM9p2xUAbna2NCdEw/) AOP (A応P), commonly known as Anime Oen Project (where "Oen" refers to cheering up someone in their native language), is a Japanese idol group consisting of 7 members (as of August 2, 2020), who love anime, debuting in 2012. The group recommends anime and talks about its appeal through TV, radio, magazines, events, and the Internet. They also frequently sing and dance to anime songs. AOP has a unique theme to their group, which is that every member is assigned a color upon becoming a part of the roster, rather than a stage name. On December 14th, 2020 the group announced that they will disband on March 31st, 2021. Members: - Yuna Asahi (旭優奈) – Member Color: Purple (パープル) - Hinaki Kudo (工藤ひなき) – Member Color: Lavender (ラベンダー) - Rin Kojima (小嶋凛) – Member Color: Yellow (イエロー) - [Yukina Tsutsumi](https://anilist.co/staff/184012) (堤雪菜) – Member Color: Light Green (ライトグリーン) - [Non Harusaki](https://anilist.co/staff/181591) (春咲暖) – Member Color: Red (レッド) - [Yuuki Hirose](https://anilist.co/staff/121025) (広瀬ゆうき) – Member Color: Orange (オレンジ) - [Seena Hoshiki](https://anilist.co/staff/172100) (星希成奏) – Member Color: Blue (ブルー) Former Members: - Yuriko Hisaki (樋崎悠里子) – Graduated: February 28, 2013 - [Misae Komori](https://anilist.co/staff/126292) (小森未彩) – Graduated: July 31, 2015 - Saki Shimizugawa (清水川沙季) – Graduated: July 31, 2015 - Marina Amane (天音まりな) – Graduated: December 31, 2015 - Saori Ogino (荻野沙織) – Graduated: March 31, 2017 - Risa Sakurana (桜奈里彩) – Graduated: March 31, 2017 - Eriko Kawakami (河上英里子) – Graduated: January 31, 2018 - [Yui Fukuo](https://anilist.co/staff/121024) (福緒唯) – Graduated: June 30, 2018 - Aoi Mizuki (水希蒼) – Graduated: March 1, 2019 - [Kei Tomoe](https://anilist.co/staff/164977) (巴奎依) – Graduated: August 2, 2020

She is a composer, arranger and synthesizer programmer.
**Fujio Akatsuka** was a pioneer Japanese artist of comical manga known as the "Gag Manga King".
__Hiromi Kikuta__ is a Japanese sound director, who works for the company Rakuonsha.

[Twitter](https://twitter.com/i/user/58120205)

Originating from [Sunrise](https://anilist.co/studio/14/).

He first came to prominence as the director who overtook [Shinji Takamatsu](https://anilist.co/staff/100152/) on [Gintama](https://anilist.co/anime/918/) from episode 100 onwards. He stepped down from the role after the [2013 movie](https://anilist.co/anime/15335/), but remained as a supervisor for the series until the end.

Also known for series such as [Osomatsu-san](https://anilist.co/anime/21261/) and [Binbougami ga!](https://anilist.co/anime/13535/).

node.description:
[Website](https://habarudo.wordpress.com/) | [Twitter](https://twitter.com/Habarudo) | [Tumblr](https://habarudo.tumblr.com/) | [DeviantArt](https://www.deviantart.com/habarudo) | [Vimeo](https://vimeo.com/habarudo) | [Sakugabooru](https://www.sakugabooru.com/user/show/288)

Norwegian animator working for [Bug Films](https://anilist.co/studio/7348/BUG-FILMS) since November 2022. Previously worked for [Juumonji](https://anilist.co/studio/6219/Juumonji) between April 2019 to October 2022.

Some of his favorite animators include [Hiroyuki Okiura](https://anilist.co/staff/103502/Hiroyuki-Okiura), [Shingo Yamashita](https://anilist.co/staff/114914/Shingo-Yamashita), [Toshiyuki Inoue](https://anilist.co/staff/103724/Toshiyuki-Inoue), [Mitsuo Iso](https://anilist.co/staff/100151/Mitsuo-Iso) and [Yutaka Nakamura](https://anilist.co/staff/101801/Yutaka-Nakamura).

Graduated from Inland Norway University of Applied Sciences with a Bachelor in Visual Arts and Design in 2016.
